{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, in the Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase, where effective spins in the low-energy infrared limit are (2k + 1)π/q, cos(qΘ) should be close to -1.",
    "In the high-T paramagnetic (PM) phase, where no long-range order persists, cos(qΘ) should average to zero.In Fig. 1, by fixing q = 6, we present the order parameters κ (top panel), cos(qΘ) (bottom panel), and the absolute value | ⟨ m⟩ | (top panel), computed via CMC for a linear system size of L = 64, as T /J 1 is varied from the Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase toward the high-T PM phase.",
    "Additionally, we include κ and | ⟨ m⟩ | obtained using anisotropic corner transfer matrix renormalization group (CTMRG) with a 4 × 4 unit cell (see main text) for comparison.",
    "The order parameters computed via CMC exhibit the expected behavior and show good agreement with the CTMRG results in the ordered Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM and Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phases.",
    "However, due to the limitations of CMC, resolving the narrow regions of the critical quasi-long-range ordered (QLRO) phase with nematic order (QLRO ⊕ Z 2 NM) and the ordered Z 2 NM phase remains challenging."
  ]
}